result for abstention (without confidenceCheck, start from 3 helper function prompt)
Abstention method : 
    - If equal (ent, rel) pair appears more than 1 times, abstain and quit.
    - If iteration is done more than n(threshold) times, abtain and quit.
    - If tail entity doesn't exist after exploreKG(), do exploreKG() process again from that point. (It can give an effect to upper 2nd abstention method)

abstention_test.py
core function : helper_function.py -> exploreKGs_abstain() / class Information() in individual_claim_info.py

Experimented by 3.5-turbo, 4o-mini

- Correct
- Wrong
- Abstain : In this case, we abstain when LLM asks equivalent (ent, rel) pair twice or more times.
- IDK : I Don't Know. This label is attached on qids which runned more than threshold iteration value (Exact iteration number in this case)
- Error : When code generates error for some reason (maybe due to parsing problem)



** gtignore files
For MetaQA two hop, there are 'X -> Y -> X' template for the question, and the true label for this template doesn't include ground truth label to it. Therefore, we have to exclude the gt_entity for prediction labels.
Also for three hop, there are 'X -> Y -> X -> Z' template, we have to exclude gt_entity for second 'X' in this case.
gtignore suffix is for this case.
